article_text:
Democrats in competitive races seem to have gotten hall passes to try to dissociate themselves from ObamaCare heading into the midterm elections, but the White House must be ruing some of the liberties their party comrades are taking with this new political independence. Witness the parade of Democrats pleading for more money for that great liberal anathema, Medicare Advantage.

The Affordable Care Act was expressly designed to restrict this successful and increasingly popular George W. Bush program that now provides 28%...
